 {"id":"bd-yx9r.5","title":"Capability, security, obligation, record, and evidence parity","description":"Several upstream families that make asupersync structurally safe are still missing or shallow in ANSI C: advanced cx capability machinery, security/authenticated surfaces, obligation and record modules, session/link/monitor layers, and evidence/evidence-sink public APIs.","design":"This epic should restore the explicit authority and proof-carrying story of the Rust crate rather than leaving only kernel internals and a few diagnostics helpers.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Missing authority/evidence/record families are represented as real public modules with coherent contracts.\\nB. Security and obligation behavior is covered by unit plus failure-path integration tests.\\nC. Session/link/monitor-style coordination surfaces no longer remain silent omissions.","notes":"Primary upstream references: src/cx/*, src/security/*, src/obligation/*, src/record/*, src/evidence.rs, src/evidence_sink.rs, src/link.rs, src/monitor.rs, and session-related exports in src/lib.rs.","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:20.291103519Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T20:41:04.190535578Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["crate-parity","cx","record","security"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.5","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:20.291103519Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.5","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:59.622791584Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.5","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:39:00.575561527Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.5","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:39:01.534808222Z","created_by"