 {"id":"bd-yx9r.5.2","title":"Port security, audit, tag, key, context, and authenticated surfaces","description":"The upstream crate exports a real security module with key/context/tag/authenticated types plus audit surfaces. The ANSI C tree needs more than minimal checks or vertical-specific instrumentation if it is going to claim comparable crate-level functionality.","design":"Port public security/audit contracts, including error taxonomy, authority context propagation, authenticated wrappers, and audit/event capture hooks that integrate with evidence/logging.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Public security/audit headers and implementations cover the upstream conceptual surface.\\nB. Unit tests cover key/tag/context handling, authenticated wrappers, and negative authorization cases.\\nC. Logged integration flows show audit/evidence output for both accepted and rejected operations.","notes":"Should integrate with C1 and C3 instead of becoming a disconnected helper island.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:21.943361044Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-14T18:48:04.754399782Z","closed_at":"2026-03-14T18:48:04.753881692Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","crate-parity","security"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.5.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:26:51.527022719Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.5.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:26:52.256469280Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.5.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:26:53.009498774Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.5.2","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.5","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:21.943361044Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metad